SIMPLE: crustiness
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Crustiness
<hw>Crust"i*ness</hw> <pr>(-⟦icr⟧-n⟦ecr⟧s)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<sn>1.</sn> <def>The state or quality of having crust or being like
crust; hardness.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>The quality of being crusty or surly.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Old Christy forgot his usual <qex>crustiness</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>W. Irving.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Crusty</ent>⟦br⟧
